.TH AIDEBUG 1 "June 2026" "aidebug 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aidebug \- AI-assisted malware reverse-engineering debugger
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aidebug
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
AIDebug performs static and optional dynamic malware-analysis triage. It maps
function-level behavior to MITRE ATT&CK, YARA candidates, IOC exports, JSON
output, and HTML analyst reports.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-binary " " FILE
Analyze a PE or ELF binary.
.TP
.BR \-\-mode " " MODE
Analysis mode: static or dynamic.
.TP
.B \-\-no-tui
Use CLI output instead of the terminal interface.
.TP
.B \-\-report
Generate an HTML report.
.TP
.B \-\-yara
Generate YARA candidate rules for high-risk findings.
.TP
.B \-\-json-export
Export analysis data as JSON.
.TP
.BR \-\-out-dir " " DIR
Write report output to DIR.
.SH EXAMPLE
.B aidebug --binary sample.exe --no-tui --report --json-export --out-dir reports/
.SH SAFETY
Use only in an isolated malware-analysis VM or authorized lab. Do not execute
unknown samples on a host operating system.
